const val title="My Resume"
const val desc="Supply Agreements: Contracts between a supplier and a buyer that outline the terms of the supply of goods or services. This could include details about pricing, delivery schedules, quality standards, and payment terms.\n" +
        "\n" +
        "Service Agreements: Contracts that define the scope of services to be provided by one business to another. These agreements often specify service levels, responsibilities, fees, and performance metrics.\n" +
        "\n" +
        "Partnership Agreements: Contracts between two or more businesses that establish a formal partnership, joint venture, or collaboration. These agreements typically outline the rights, responsibilities, profit-sharing arrangements, and exit strategies for the partners.\n" +
        "\n" +
        "Non-Disclosure Agreements (NDAs): Contracts that protect confidential information shared between businesses during discussions or negotiations. NDAs prohibit the recipient from disclosing or using the information for unauthorized purposes.\n" +
        "\n" +
        "Licensing Agreements: Contracts that grant one business the right to use another business's intellectual property, such as patents, trademarks, or copyrights, for a specified purpose and under certain conditions.\n" +
        "\n" +
        "Franchise Agreements: Contracts that allow one business (the franchisee) to operate under the brand, systems, and support of another business (the franchisor) in exchange for fees and adherence to established standards.\n" +
        "\n" +
        "Sales Agreements: Contracts that govern the sale of goods or services from one business to another. These agreements specify the terms of the sale, including pricing, delivery, warranties, and payment terms.\n" +
        "\n" +
        "B2B contracts are essential for clarifying the rights and obligations of each party involved in a business transaction. They help minimize misunderstandings, disputes, and legal liabilities, ensuring that both parties are on the same page regarding the terms of their agreement. B2B contracts are typically more complex than consumer contracts due to the unique and often intricate nature of business relationships and transactions."